<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>8 Digital Tech â€“ Introduction to Pygame Zero</title><link>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/8/games/02introduction/</link><description>Recent content in Introduction to Pygame Zero on 8 Digital Tech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><atom:link href="https://tmcdigitech.github.io/8/games/02introduction/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Games: 01: The window</title><link>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/8/games/02introduction/01window/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/8/games/02introduction/01window/</guid><description>
&lt;p>You can set the size of your game window using the &lt;code>WIDTH&lt;/code> and &lt;code>HEIGHT&lt;/code> constants.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>WIDTH &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">100&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>HEIGHT &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">200&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;img src="01.png" alt="A 100x200 window">&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>WIDTH &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">700&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>HEIGHT &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">100&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;img src="02.png" alt="A 700x100 window">&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Games: 02: Drawing things</title><link>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/8/games/02introduction/02draw/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tmcdigitech.github.io/8/games/02introduction/02draw/</guid><description>
&lt;p>You can draw things by putting commands inside a function called &lt;code>draw()&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-python" data-lang="python">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>WIDTH &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">400&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>HEIGHT &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">300&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">def&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#50fa7b">draw&lt;/span>():
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> screen&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">.&lt;/span>draw&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">.&lt;/span>circle((&lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">100&lt;/span>,&lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">100&lt;/span>), &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">50&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;red&amp;#39;&lt;/span>)
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> screen&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">.&lt;/span>draw&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">.&lt;/span>filled_circle((&lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">300&lt;/span>,&lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">100&lt;/span>), &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">25&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;yellow&amp;#39;&lt;/span>)
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> screen&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">.&lt;/span>draw&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">.&lt;/span>line((&lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">200&lt;/span>,&lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">200&lt;/span>), (&lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">180&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#bd93f9">80&lt;/span>), &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;green&amp;#39;&lt;/span>)
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>
&lt;p>$$
\mathtt{screen.draw.circle(\colorbox{yellow}{(100,100)}, \colorbox{aquamarine}{50}, \colorbox{pink}{'red'})}
$$&lt;/p>
&lt;p>$$\mathtt{screen.draw.circle(\colorbox{yellow}{(100,100)}, \colorbox{aquamarine}{50}, \colorbox{pink}{&amp;lsquo;red&amp;rsquo;})$$&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="03.png" alt="a circle, a filled circle, and a line">&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>